<li id="cite_note-WorldPrisonBrief-5"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-WorldPrisonBrief_5-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-WorldPrisonBrief_5-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-WorldPrisonBrief_5-2"><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-WorldPrisonBrief_5-3"><sup><i><b>d</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.prisonstudies.org/highest-to-lowest">Highest to Lowest</a>. <a href="/wiki/World_Prison_Brief" title="World Prison Brief">World Prison Brief</a> (WPB). Use the dropdown menu to choose lists of countries by region or the whole world. Use the menu to select highest-to-lowest lists of prison population totals, prison population rates, percentage of pre-trial detainees/remand imprisoned people, percentage of imprisoned females, percentage of imprisoned foreign people, and occupancy rate. Column headings in WPB tables can be clicked to reorder columns lowest to highest, or alphabetically. For detailed information for each country click on any country name in lists. See also the <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.prisonstudies.org/world-prison-brief-data">WPB main data page</a> and click on the map links and/or the sidebar links to get to the region and country desired.</span>
