<li id="cite_note-cpusa2015-126"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-cpusa2015_126-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.bjs.gov/index.cfm?ty=pbdetail&amp;iid=5870">Correctional Populations in the United States, 2015</a>. By Danielle Kaeble and Lauren Glaze, <i>BJS Statisticians.</i> Dec. 2016. <a href="/wiki/Bureau_of_Justice_Statistics" title="Bureau of Justice Statistics">Bureau of Justice Statistics</a>. See <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.bjs.gov/content/pub/pdf/cpus15.pdf">PDF</a>. Page 2 says: "At yearend 2015, an estimated 2,173,800 persons were either under the jurisdiction of state or federal prisons or in the custody of local jails in the United States".</span>
